There is, moreover, very little in this chapter to correspond to the account of Tacitus, the similar items of information being of the most commonplace character and partly found in Caesar.

Under these circumstances, it is quite superfluous to discuss at any length the alleged stylistic influence of Mela upon Tacitus.
